description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Night Cleaners needed Urgently!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for people to help increase the number of Domestic cleaning staff across the wards within &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are happy to roll your sleeves up and help, we need you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals manages the &lt;strong&gt;temporary &lt;/strong&gt;work placement (bank) at The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust, and we are looking for cleaners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotherham Hospital which is situated just two miles south of Rotherham town centre, within proximity to the M1 and M18 motorways, six miles from Sheffield and close to Doncaster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They need your help whether you have experience as a cleaner or have had cleaning responsibilities as part of your role. If you would like to help the fight against COVID-19, we have a possible role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title&lt;/strong&gt;: Domestic Cleaners&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;Rotherham Hospital, Moorgate Road, Rotherham, S60 2UD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt;Facilities Department working across various wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay rate&lt;/strong&gt;: £9.21 - £12.98 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt;26/10/2020 to 30/04/2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours of Work&lt;/strong&gt;: 22.00pm – 06.00am, worked over 4nights on and 4 nights off over a 7-day period working alternate shift pattern with another cleaner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role may involve working directly on COVID-19 wards.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training and PPE will be provided and if you or your family have symptoms you will be prioritised for COVID – 19 testing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This roles duties &amp; responsibilities include: -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide a clean and safe environment for patients, visitors, and colleagues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning duties such as vacuuming, mopping, dusting, cleaning toilet and shower areas, cleaning surfaces i.e windows, doors, beds, chairs etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring all equipment used is fully maintained, cleaned, and stored appropriately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To use resources efficiently and effectively for each cleaning task.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The key skills and knowledge they are looking for: -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning experience (desirable, not essential)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of COSHH &amp; colour coding system (desirable, not essential)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Both written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow instructions and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pay attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take responsibility for their own work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to work unsupervised&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF SUCCESSFUL&lt;/strong&gt; – you will be contacted to discuss the role in more detail and then register with us before attending between 1 to 2 days of paid training before starting the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Pay Rates - work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First choice of placements at over 50 NHS Trusts in England&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated consultants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free DBS and free training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build holiday allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 126,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over &lt;strong&gt;£70 million&lt;/strong&gt; each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Register today for various flexible working options and long-term placement opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclaimer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
